> So, I'll try asking them about icon/logo and its license via Twitter :)

Cool! Please, don't forget to mention the support in the upcoming version of NetBeans, maybe they can promote it a bit ;)

@ondrejmirtes @junichi11

It is up to a user to decide on which file(s) (scope) to run the given tool. I guess we could perhaps show a "warning" if anything else than a project is selected - right, Junichi? Any place is good I guess (any run dialog and/or window with results).

Thanks.

@junichi11 

Junichi, not sure whether it is possible but we could try - if the scope is other then a project (or a project directory), use PHPStan to ask for dependent files and add them to the files to be analuyzed. That should be possible I hope, right? Or, if we can, just do not allow to analyze individual files using PHPStan (no idea whether it is supported by the `php.code.analysis` API/SPI).

Thanks.

@tmysik 
> Exactly. But we need to handle also PHPStan versions that do not have this feature yet (it means all PHPStan versions currently :). If there was a PHPStan parameter for it, that could help us (something like: run it with the param and if it fails, it means that it is some older version so run it once more without the param).

Yes :)

Travis fails because http://hg.netbeans.org/binaries/ is down.

